{"page":1,"results":[{"adult":false,"gender":2,"id":50767,"known_for_department":"Directing","name":"Craig Gillespie","original_name":"Craig Gillespie","popularity":0.9141,"profile_path":"/pVHspL9QWsXCm3t3VXEaCJ9y8Zz.jpg","known_for":[{"adult":false,"backdrop_path":"/6MKr3KgOLmzOP6MSuZERO41Lpkt.jpg","id":337404,"title":"Cruella","original_title":"Cruella","overview":"In 1970s London amidst the punk rock revolution, a young grifter named Estella is determined to make a name for herself with her designs. She befriends a pair of young thieves who appreciate her appetite for mischief, and together they are able to build a life for themselves on the London streets. One day, Estella’s flair for fashion catches the eye of the Baroness von Hellman, a fashion legend who is devastatingly chic and terrifyingly haute. But their relationship sets in motion a course of events and revelations that will cause Estella to embrace her wicked side and become the raucous, fashionable and revenge-bent Cruella.","poster_path":"/hjS9mH8KvRiGHgjk6VUZH7OT0Ng.jpg","media_type":"movie","original_language":"en","genre_ids":[35,80,18],"popularity":16.6362,"release_date":"2021-05-26","softcore":false,"video":false,"vote_average":7.971,"vote_count":10070},{"adult":false,"backdrop_path":"/5owIV2sqdfILBKyOOIkLYVqanZp.jpg","id":389015,"title":"I, Tonya","original_title":"I, Tonya","overview":"Competitive ice skater Tonya Harding rises amongst the ranks at the U.S. Figure Skating Championships, but her future in the sport is thrown into doubt when her ex-husband intervenes.","poster_path":"/6gNXwSHxaksR1PjVZRqNapmkgj3.jpg","media_type":"movie","original_language":"en","genre_ids":[18,35],"popularity":4.2541,"release_date":"2017-12-07","softcore":false,"video":false,"vote_average":7.47,"vote_count":6194},{"adult":false,"backdrop_path":"/llSmoD6mmfIQIQspwbckAYd110Z.jpg","id":58151,"title":"Fright Night","original_title":"Fright Night","overview":"A teenager suspects his new neighbour is a vampire. Unable to convince anyone, he tries to enlist the help of a self-proclaimed vampire hunter and magician.","poster_path":"/ySQ3v4Fzpy3fePs86eoLiDzwLYM.jpg","media_type":"movie","original_language":"en","genre_ids":[27,35],"popularity":4.7819,"release_date":"2011-08-18","softcore":false,"video":false,"vote_average":6.239,"vote_count":2120}]},{"adult":false,"gender":0,"id":3545688,"known_for_department":"Acting","name":"Craig Gillespie","original_name":"Craig Gillespie","popularity":0.085,"profile_path":null,"known_for":[{"adult":false,"backdrop_path":"/4KkwQSRbqjSPQLpDUtpptsE4jLE.jpg","id":2306,"name":"The Man from Snowy River","original_name":"The Man from Snowy River","overview":"The Man from Snowy River is an Australian television series based on Banjo Paterson's poem \"The Man from Snowy River\". Released in Australia as Banjo Paterson's The Man from Snowy River, the series was subsequently released in both the United States and the United Kingdom as Snowy River: The McGregor Saga.\n\nThe television series has no relationship to the 1982 film The Man from Snowy River or the 1988 sequel The Man from Snowy River II. Instead, the series follows the adventures of Matt McGregor, a successful squatter, and his family. Matt is the hero immortalized in Banjo Paterson's poem \"The Man from Snowy River\", and the series is set 25 years after his famous ride.","poster_path":"/9ez7SBvFq5nIAmQ8BVwdohIGf1x.jpg","media_type":"tv","original_language":"en","genre_ids":[18,37],"popularity":10.5144,"first_air_date":"1994-09-23","softcore":false,"vote_average":6.833,"vote_count":12,"origin_country":["AU"]},{"adult":false,"backdrop_path":"/v24AJ7GZULrdDx9nRTezaxUOEuG.jpg","id":2233,"name":"Blue Heelers","original_name":"Blue Heelers","overview":"Blue Heelers was one of Australia's longest running weekly television drama series.  Blue Heelers is a police drama series set in the fictional country town of Mount Thomas. Under the watchful eye of Tom Croydon (John Wood), the men and women of Mount Thomas Police Station fight crime, resolve disputes and tackle the social issues of the day.  We watch their successes and their failures and learn to grow with them and their loved ones as the heart of the series develops.","poster_path":"/dxCyxmFSHiAonsb94s1QScyHBAk.jpg","media_type":"tv","original_language":"en","genre_ids":[18],"popularity":24.151,"first_air_date":"1993-09-10","softcore":false,"vote_average":6.469,"vote_count":16,"origin_country":["AU"]},{"adult":false,"backdrop_path":null,"id":10561,"name":"Janus","original_name":"Janus","overview":"Janus is an Australian drama television series screened on the Australian Broadcasting Corporation in 1994 and 1995. Two series were produced, with a total of 26 episodes.\n\nJanus was a spin-off series from the earlier ABC-TV crime series Phoenix.\n\nLoosely based on the true story of Melbourne's Pettingill family and the Walsh Street police shootings, Janus follows the bitterly-fought prosecutions of a notorious criminal family, the Hennesseys, from the viewpoints of the family, the police and, in particular, the lawyers, prosecutors, barristers and judges involved in all aspects of the story.\n\nWhen the series begins, four members of the infamous Hennessey clan are acquitted of the shooting of two young policemen in a bungled bank heist. The city of Melbourne is shocked as brothers Mal and Steve, along with brother-in-law Darren Mack and friend Ken Hardy, walk free.\n\nThe prosecutors, judges, magistrates and police—many modelled heavily on real-life legal figures—are determined to put the Hennessey members behind bars if they can. But corruption, legal loopholes, delays, and stretched resources combine to make the quest to jail the group far from straightforward.","poster_path":"/uOVsNtECSWbRFgYw1Nzb9Bxy7zs.jpg","media_type":"tv","original_language":"en","genre_ids":[18,80],"popularity":6.1962,"first_air_date":"1994-09-01","softcore":false,"vote_average":9.0,"vote_count":2,"origin_country":["AU"]}]},{"adult":false,"gender":2,"id":2009040,"known_for_department":"Crew","name":"Craig Gillespie","original_name":"Craig Gillespie","popularity":1.5987,"profile_path":null,"known_for":[{"adult":false,"backdrop_path":"/eCynaAOgYYiw5yN5lBwz3IxqvaW.jpg","id":12,"title":"Finding Nemo","original_title":"Finding Nemo","overview":"Nemo, an adventurous young clownfish, is unexpectedly taken from his Great Barrier Reef home to a dentist's office aquarium. It's up to his worrisome father Marlin and a friendly but forgetful fish Dory to bring Nemo home -- meeting vegetarian sharks, surfer dude turtles, hypnotic jellyfish, hungry seagulls, and more along the way.","poster_path":"/5lc6nQc0VhWFYFbNv016xze8Jvy.jpg","media_type":"movie","original_language":"en","genre_ids":[16,10751,12],"popularity":19.388,"release_date":"2003-05-30","softcore":false,"video":false,"vote_average":7.819,"vote_count":20571}]}],"total_pages":1,"total_results":3}